entries.femaleVariant: You're, uh, you're the Padre, right? I'm V.
entries.maleVariant: You're, uh, the Padre, right? I'm, uh, I'm V.

entries.femaleVariant: [Lean] Padre?
[Lean] Hey, Padre.
Here to say goodbye to one of your own, Padre?
entries.maleVariant: You, uh, here to say goodbye to one of your own, Padre?

entries.femaleVariant: You believe in life after death?
So, Padre. You think Jackie's looking down upon us... from up there?
How're things in the streets?
I'm here to say goodbye to a good man.
This is not the place to conduct business. Have some respect.
I believe he has met God, stood before Him.
Sebastian Ibarra. I have heard of you, about you.
They say there's an echo in Heywood. You say one thing, you hear it a few more times after.
Jackie – did ya know him well?
entries.maleVariant: Jackie, uh – did ya know him well?

entries.femaleVariant: Did you know Jackie well?
That so?
I remember the day his mother brought him into this world. The day his father left. The day he took you into his home.
Yes, V. I knew him quite well.
That's it?
I don't know if God left the meeting happy, but I'm pretty certain Jackie did.
How are things on the street?
[Step away] Time I was on my way.
I'm 'onna move on.
Go with God.
